---------------------------------------------------------<br>
Fear is not a zone to be &quot;broken&quot;. The easiest way to do fear is to do it this way.<br>
<br>
1)First off have an understanding guild.<br>
2) Break in. Have 2-3 groups zone in invised and run to the west wall.(ps-should have 4-5 groups prolly)<br>
3) KILL all mobs there.<br>
3b) If you get wiped out or begin to get wiped out have the last groups zone in and finish it off.<br>
3c) if EVERYONE dies (which the monk should NOT.) Drag all corpses to the wall so that no mobs can get aggroed while you ress.<br>
**<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Highlight this one</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
4) DO NOT FIEGN DEATH.<br>
5) When you pull go get some mobs and bring them back to camp. Always have Spirit of Eagle on.<br>
6) If you aggro 6 or so mobs run to camp and kill what ever you bring. <br>
7) When you have less than 2 mobs in camp run back out and bring what ever comes.<br>
8 ) You have successfully started to auto-pull. See any mobs that DONT come back will spread aggro to the rest of the zone. The zone will be all crazy and when you get within an area of some mobs they will begin to chase you.<br>
9) Remember pathing sucks and make sure you bring enough.<br>
10) If the enchanters complain about mana, keep pulling.<br>
11) If the clerics complain about mana, keep pulling.<br>
12) if the WARRIORS start to complain about mana, slow down a bit.. <br>
13) after about an hour or so of this non stop pulling, fighting FD for once. ( i know this goes against rule 4 but depending on your guild or group in fear you dont wanna run them out of juice.)<br>
14) /q or log our and come back in after you have FDed so that you can start fresh.<br>
15) feel free to move out to the bell if you have cleared everything else out.<br>
16) if it takes longer than 3 hours to clear fear your doing something wrong.<br>
<br>
THAT my friends is how i pull fear. Normal fear raid is about 2 and a half hours unless we all die (except for me, remember YOU have to be there to CR.) then its about 3 hours max.<br>
<br>
