<br>
Actually, a monk makes one of the best pullers for Fear if used in conjunction with a good Ranger.  There are many instances where having a duo pulling works out better for the whole raid.<br>
<br>
-After initial break, many of the areas are clumps of mobs.  Have monk slowly walk up to area (such as FF tower, TD house, Scareling/Jacko tower, etc) until mobs aggro. Wait till they get in range and FD, then have Ranger pick off one or two of them when others wander away.<br>
<br>
-Many times a Ranger will get into trouble (any class for that matter) with mobs such as the toads, eyes, and gorgons.  If monk is near the monk can usually aggro these mobs off the Ranger if he is rooted, feared, or stunned.  Vice versa for the monk, Nyklon saved my tail many times.<br>
<br>
-TT bridge/Graveyard is so easy to split up with a monk/ranger tandem.<br>
<br>
-Constant, steadier pulls with a good tandem and not clumps of 5+ mobs at a time that create downtime for a raid.<br>
<br>
